e the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":34,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Goodrich was born in 1515, in Felsham, Suffolk, England. He had at least 1 daughter with Susan Shepherd. He died in 1554, in Suffolk, England, at the age of 39."},"et":{"1515–1554":"1515–1554","1524–Female":"1524–Surnud","1537–1580":"1537–1580","1524":"1524","1554":"1554","1580":"1580","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","1537":"1537","Thurloxton, Somerset, England":"Thurloxton, Somerset, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Felsham, Suffolk, England":"Felsham, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1515–1554":"1515–1554","1524–Female":"1524–Kuollut","1537–1580":"1537–1580","1524":"1524","1554":"1554","1580":"1580","1549":"1549","1515":"1515","1537":"1537","Thurloxton, Somerset, England":"Thurloxton, Somerset, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Felsham, Suffolk, England":"Felsham, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1515–1554":"1515–1554","1524–Female":"1524–Décédée","1537–1580":"1537–158